Country reactions included containment measures, such as quarantines (also known as home confinement orders, home containment orders or lockdowns) and pick-up touches. On April 2, about 300 million people (almost 90% of the population) are somehow confined in the United States, more than 50 million people are confined in the Philippines, around 59 million people are confined in South Africa and 1.3 billion people are confined in India.
